%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "content-type"}/
    %title Hue/Saturation/Lightness
    /
      Demonstration of using HSL format for colors. Also demonstrates use of 'inherit' keyword value for
      properties.
    :css
      * {
        padding: 20px;
        /* Both of these produce white: */
        color: hsl(28, 37%, 100%);
        background-color: hsl(156, 40%, 100%);
      }

      .black1 {
        background-color: hsl(245, 63%, 0%);
      }

      .black2 {
        background-color: hsl(59, 20%, 0%);
      }

      p {
        color: hsl(10, 50%, 70%);
        font-size: 20px;
        font-weight: bold;
        background-color: inherit;
      }
  %body.black1
    .white
      .black2
